## D9: Search endpoint with configurable search_type — 2026-03-23

**Context**: Need to decide where hybrid search fusion logic lives while maintaining constitution principle that all DB ops go through edge functions

**Question**: [Question not provided]

**Options Considered**:
1. Postgres RPC for all search (single trip); 2. Edge function composition (two trips, flexible); 3. Configurable search_type parameter

**Decision**: Single search edge function with search_type parameter (hybrid|fts|vector, default hybrid). Hybrid uses Postgres RPC function for single-trip fusion. FTS and vector are separate queries available for consumers who want custom ranking.

**Rationale**: Defaults to most performant path (Postgres RPC hybrid). Power users can call FTS/vector independently and compose their own ranking. All paths go through edge functions per constitution.

**Implications**:
[Implications not provided]

**Stories Affected**: Story 2, Story 7

**Related Questions**: [Questions not specified]

